load on the DNS servers.\\n32:  *\\n33:  * <p>Key features:\\n34:  * <ul>\\n35:  *   <li>Thread pool sharing for various Pulsar operations (IO, timer, lookup, etc.)</li>\\n36:  *   <li>Shared DNS resolver and cache</li>\\n37:  *   <li>Resource lifecycle management</li>\\n38:  * </ul>\\n39:  *\\n40:  * <p>Usage example:\\n41:  * <pre>{@code\\n42:  * // To share all possible resources across multiple PulsarClient instances\\n43:  * PulsarClientSharedResources sharedResources = PulsarClientSharedResources.builder()\\n44:  *     .build();\\n45:  * // Use these resources with multiple PulsarClient instances\\n46:  * PulsarClient client1 = PulsarClient.builder().sharedResources(sharedResources).build();\\n47:  * PulsarClient client2 = PulsarClient.builder().sharedResources(sharedResources).build();\\n48:  * client1.close();\\n49:  * client2.close();\\n50:  * sharedResources.close();\\n51:  * }</pre>\\n52:  *\\n53:  * <p>The instance should be created using the {@link PulsarClientSharedResourcesBuilder},\\n54:  * which can be obtained via the {@link #builder()} method.\\n55:  *\\n56:  * @see PulsarClientSharedResourcesBuilder\\n57:  * @see SharedResource\\n58:  */\\n59: public interface PulsarClientSharedResources extends AutoCloseable {\\n60:     enum SharedResource {\\n61:         // pulsar-io threadpool\\n62:         EventLoopGroup(SharedResourceType.EventLoopGroup),\\n63:         // pulsar-external-listener threadpool\\n64:         ListenerExecutor(SharedResourceType.ThreadPool),\\n65:         // pulsar-timer threadpool\\n66:         Timer(SharedResourceType.Timer),\\n67:         // pulsar-client-internal threadpool\\n68:         InternalExecutor(SharedResourceType.ThreadPool),\\n69:         // pulsar-client-scheduled threadpool\\n70:         ScheduledExecutor(SharedResourceType.ThreadPool),\\n71:         // pulsar-lookup threadpool\\n72:         LookupExecutor(SharedResourceType.ThreadPool),\\n73:         // DNS resolver and cache that must be shared together with eve